body:
### Version

Yosys 0.33+53 (git sha1 e2b613355, clang 14.0.0-1ubuntu1.1 -fPIC -Os)

### On which OS did this happen?

Linux

### Reproduction Steps

Verilog file `top.v`:
```verilog
module top;
wire \0a , \a ;
endmodule
```
Yosys script:
```
read_verilog top.v
hierarchy -check -top top
write_json top.json
```

### Expected Behavior

All identifiers either have the leading "\\", or none of them have it.

### Actual Behavior

`top.json` generated by Yosys:
```json
{
  "creator": "Yosys 0.33+53 (git sha1 e2b613355, clang 14.0.0-1ubuntu1.1 -fPIC -Os)",
  "modules": {
    "top": {
      "attributes": {
        "top": "00000000000000000000000000000001",
        "src": "top.v:1.1-3.10"
      },
      "ports": {
      },
      "cells": {
      },
      "netnames": {
        "\\0a": {
          "hide_name": 0,
          "bits": [ 2 ],
          "attributes": {
            "src": "top.v:2.6-2.9"
          }
        },
        "a": {
          "hide_name": 0,
          "bits": [ 3 ],
          "attributes": {
            "src": "top.v:2.12-2.14"
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
```

One of the netnames is "\\\\0a", while the other is "a".
